video_description: If you want to improve the lighting in your videos and make your content look high quality, but don't know where to start, the best thing you can do is invest in a bright, high-quality light like the G60 from Zhiyun. Cheap clip-on lights from Amazon have poor color accuracy and are not as bright as you think they are.  My recommendation is to either use natural outdoor lighting, sit in front of a window, or step up to something like this mini G60 COB LED video light, which has professional level features for when you're ready to upgrade to a softbox. The G60 is the smallest COB light currently available and is a great companion for taking with you on the go because it can be USB powered or plugged into a wall outlet.
